{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17412666","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17412666"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-28T07:34:55+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-28T07:33:41+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261066"}},"session":{"data":{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261066"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18923"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17567049","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17567049"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":0,"answeredAt":"2025-09-29T23:53:32+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-29T23:53:32+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18923"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questionSessions","id":"1261066","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionSessions/1261066"},"attributes":{"startedAt":"2025-09-28T07:33:14+09:30","updatedAt":"2025-09-28T07:38:50+09:30","sessionType":"qbank","questionStatus":"all","difficulty":[],"timeLimit":null,"questionCount":2,"questionsAnswered":1,"marksTotal":1,"marksAttainable":1,"marksAttempted":1,"finishedAt":"2025-09-28T07:37:39+09:30","resultsAvailable":true,"score":0,"questionsCorrect":0,"marksCorrect":0},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"pack":{"data":{"type":"packs","id":"5"}},"exam":{"data":null}}},{"type":"questions","id":"18923","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/18923"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.43,0.03,0.29,0.07,0.18]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11656"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"95078"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"11656","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/11656"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18923"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"78045"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"6"},{"type":"tags","id":"24"},{"type":"tags","id":"25"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"72"},{"type":"tags","id":"76"},{"type":"tags","id":"1484"},{"type":"tags","id":"1643"},{"type":"tags","id":"3343"},{"type":"tags","id":"4977"},{"type":"tags","id":"4990"},{"type":"tags","id":"5326"},{"type":"tags","id":"5425"},{"type":"tags","id":"5428"},{"type":"tags","id":"5631"},{"type":"tags","id":"5649"},{"type":"tags","id":"11260"},{"type":"tags","id":"11296"},{"type":"tags","id":"11626"},{"type":"tags","id":"11650"},{"type":"tags","id":"12867"},{"type":"tags","id":"12917"},{"type":"tags","id":"12919"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"27412"},{"type":"contributions","id":"27458"},{"type":"contributions","id":"31841"},{"type":"contributions","id":"32638"},{"type":"contributions","id":"43709"},{"type":"contributions","id":"45086"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"95078","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/95078"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003EWhile working in the Emergency Department, you assess an 82-year-old woman from a residential aged care facility who presents with confusion. During examination for a suspected urinary tract infection, you notice multiple bruises in different stages of healing on her arms and torso. The facility staff member accompanying her states that she has not noticed any of the injuries previously.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes the mandatory reporting obligation in this situation?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Document findings and inform facility manager","Request explanation from other aged care staff members","Notify police within 24 hours","Arrange geriatric medicine review","Report to Aged Care Quality and Safety Commission only"],"correctOptions":[2],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003EThe most appropriate action is to \u003Cstrong\u003Enotify police within 24 hours\u003C/strong\u003E. In Australia, the requirements for reporting elder abuse in aged care settings are primarily governed by federal legislation, specifically the Aged Care Act 1997. This Act mandates that healthcare workers have a mandatory obligation to report suspected physical or sexual abuse of residents in aged care facilities to police within 24 hours of developing reasonable suspicion.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe Aged Care Act 1997 defines reportable assaults as:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003EUnreasonable use of force against a resident\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003EUnlawful or inappropriate sexual contact with a resident\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options are inappropriate because:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EDocument findings and inform facility manager\u003C/strong\u003E - While documentation is important, it does not fulfill mandatory reporting obligations. Documentation should be thorough but should not delay mandatory reporting.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ERequest explanation from other aged care staff members\u003C/strong\u003E - This may compromise investigation and delay appropriate reporting.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EArrange geriatric medicine review\u003C/strong\u003E - While medical assessment is important, suspected abuse requires immediate mandatory reporting.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EReport to Aged Care Quality and Safety Commission only\u003C/strong\u003E - Additional reporting to the Aged Care Quality and Safety Commission can occur but does not replace the requirement for police notification.\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003EIt\u0027s important to note that in Australia, aged care is governed by the federal government, and therefore the requirements are based on federal laws, not state-based laws. If this situation occurred in a community setting rather than a residential aged care facility, reporting requirements would vary by state and territory.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EElder abuse is a significant public health issue that includes physical abuse, sexual abuse, psychological abuse, financial exploitation and neglect. Physical abuse, which may present as unexplained injuries, bruising, or fractures, is one of the most readily identifiable forms. Healthcare workers play a crucial role in recognising and reporting suspected abuse to protect vulnerable older adults.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Elder abuse includes physical, sexual, psychological, financial abuse and neglect, with physical abuse being one of the most readily identifiable forms.","Healthcare workers must report suspected physical or sexual abuse in residential aged care facilities to police within 24 hours under the Aged Care Act 1997.","Mandatory reporting applies to both witnessed incidents and reasonable suspicion of abuse in aged care settings.","Reports of suspected elder abuse can also be made to the Aged Care Quality and Safety Commission in addition to police notification."],"references":["Abuse of older people. In: White Book, Specific abuse issues for adults and older people, RACGP [online]. 2022; cited 2025 Jan 18. Available at: https://www.racgp.org.au/clinical-resources/clinical-guidelines/key-racgp-guidelines/view-all-racgp-guidelines/abuse-and-violence/specific-abuse-issues-for-adults-and-older-people/abuse-of-older-people","Aged Care Quality and Safety Commission. Serious incidents. 2023. Available from: https://www.agedcarequality.gov.au/older-australians/safety-care/serious-incidents"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"78045"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"18923"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"78045","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/78045"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2025-03-27T09:43:08+10:30","updatedAt":"2025-03-27T09:44:33+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"11656"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"95078"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"6","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/6"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc75","name":"Geriatrics","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"24","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/24"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\ude91","name":"Emergency Medicine","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"5"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"25","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/25"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83d\udc68\u200d\ud83d\udc69\u200d\ud83d\udc66","name":"General Practice","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"6"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"67","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/67"},"attributes":{"emoji":"","name":"Basic Science","synonyms":null,"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":null},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"5